en_83585_0	In conformity with directions, issued by the acting Chief of Defence Staff and Commander of the Army, the Officer Career Development Centre (OCDC) at Buttala organized a lecture on ‘Women’s Rights’ as part of its weekly training Day programme for Other Ranks on Wednesday (12).
en_83585_1	Captain H.M.D.S Senarathne of 2 Sri Lanka Army General Services Corps (2SLAGSC) delivered the lecture for them at the invitation of the OCDC Commandant, Major General Jayanath Jayaweera.
en_83585_2	The purpose of this endeavour was to give a basic understanding on how women should be treated equally as men and prevent woman harassment in the working environment.
en_83585_3	Legal rights of women which have been guaranteed in the Sri Lankan Constitution, including the main aspects such as gender equality, legal framework to protect women’s rights, the types of violence women have to undergo inside working places as well as in the society and also the domestic violence in the Sri Lankan context were covered during the lecture.
en_83585_4	The Commandant of OCDC and the members of the permanent staff also participated in the session.
